27/11/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- In a statement Monday (November 26th), Krisztina Nagy, spokeswoman for EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn, said the Union applauds the political dialogue that resumed in BiH last week when leaders of the six largest parties in parliament met in a bid to resolve the ongoing crisis. Nagy added that the EU agrees it is crucial for the government and parliament to begin functioning again to tackle huge challenges, including EU integration. Nagy also reiterated support for the Mostar police reform declaration and its accompanying action plan, which was adopted by the six leaders.
In other news, Monday, EUFOR announced that Rear Admiral Hans-Jochen Witthauer is wrapping up his term as commander. His successor will be Spanish Major General Ignacio Martin Villalain. (Nezavisne Novine - 27/11/07; RTRS, Fena, EUFOR press release - 26/11/07)
